Hauls and mukbangs were me disrespecting myself. It was greed, gluttony and wrath and it was ugly to me. So I’m sorry if anyone misses “the old trish” cause I certainly do not. YouTube slowing down has been a blessing. I still post cause I love it. Cooking, baby, etc

I’ve always loved making money and having nice things but I love spending quality time with the people I love more. I like making people happy. I love making myself happy. At the height of making money, I was causing chaos and drama and anxiety for so many people. I hated it

Ppl ever stop to think, there are more important things in life than having a career. Yes, we need money to survive (as do I) but the minute I put my own happiness over how much money I could make, is the day I finally felt peace and contentment

Chasing views caused me anxiety and others grief. Chasing views meant chasing money which led me down a path of trolling,drama and hurt. I was rewarded with a stable mind, inner peace, self love ….and now with a child of my own. I wanted to have a child for so long but it was like the universe was waiting for me to heal and discover this secret. And it was a journey.

…people laughed at me, some even criticised me for “mocking” spiritual teachings. While others judged me, I kept my peace. And in that found my center. Connected with the non physical. Honed my strength, protected my power. And life then rewarded me with things I had been missin

…I did therapy, took meds, etc. it worked a little but not deeply. It wasn’t until last year when I went on a spiritual journey, exploring all teachings, practices and religions, that I found my answers - in all of the above….

I hated myself, I hated my life for so long and it seeped out into everything I did. Lost friendships, lost jobs, but I couldn’t help myself. I was so miserable, I wanted everyone to feel it too. Until I hit rock bottom after rock bottom and one day it clicked …
